    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-06T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-06T12:00:00-05:00" n="111"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/3238</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EMF1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Egan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-06T18:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1917, 6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.05 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>439. To-day at 5 o’clock the Foreign Minister brought me the following: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>I authorize you to communicate to your Government that in the opinion of
                            the Danish Government the position of Denmark both actually and formally
                            is so different from that of the United States <pb facs="0289" n="117"
                                xml:id="pg_117"/> that it is not possible to draw an analogy from
                            the one to the other, and further that the three northern governments
                            are in consultation with one another at Stockholm in order to fix on a
                            basis of international law the attitude to be taken by them on account
                            of the new German regulations.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_EMF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Egan</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
